
Download and install the vscode: https://code.visualstudio.com/download

Download and install anaconda: https://www.anaconda.com/download/success

Open the colab using this link: https://colab.research.google.com/

Python download and installation link: https://www.python.org/downloads/

Note: Download python version at least 3.10 or more than that

If python and vs code and anaconda is not ready inside your system you can work with colab

Go and search python in your vs code extension and download the microsoft python extension

Click on view > open command pallet > select python interpreter > select base interpreter(this interpreter from anaconda)


If anaconda is not there inside your system then what you will do Download and install anacond
a: https://www.anaconda.com/download/success


Steps for creating and activating the virtual env:

Conda create -p venv python=3.10 -y
Conda activate <path of your virtual env>


We have to create and install the requirement file : pip install -r requirements.txt
